               <head>Miscellaneous works on Euclidian geometry, 4 items (a-d)</head>
               <msContents class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh85054134 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85068424">
                  <summary>Miscellaneous collection of works on Euclidian geometry written by Imām al-Dīn Riyāz̤ī ibn Luṭf Allāh Muhandis Dihlavī Darbī. Several inscriptions suggest these are the author’s autograph, but this claim might be doubtful due to the erratic nature of the hand and copious corrections in margins. Volume not dated; items a and c dated separately (1130-2/1718-20). Rough naskh. Pencil foliation. Lacking original binding. Paper dust wrapper. Folios mostly unbound; cropped, stains, wormholes, later repairs. Condition fragile.</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="ar" otherLangs="fa">Arabic and Persian</textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1441A-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="23v">ff. 1v-23v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1441A(a), ff. 1v-23v.</p>
                        <p>Persian translation by 
                <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100043782133.0x000001 viaf_51546611" role="aut">Imām al-Dīn Riyāz̤ī ibn Luṭf Allāh Muhandis Dihlavī Darbī</persName>of an earlier Arabic compendium on 
                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_176184097" role="aut">Euclid</persName>, the 
                <title key="work_23021">Ashkāl al-taʾsīs</title>by 
                <persName key="viaf_107495244" role="ant">Shams al-Dīn Samarqandī</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>The work was completed in 1111/1699-1700 with the intention of being presented as a gift in the majlis or gathering of the noble, 
                <persName key="person_f8106" role="dte">Muḥammad Yār Khān</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>The work comprises a muqaddimah and thirty-five diagrams.</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 23v): completed 1130/1718.</p>
                        <p>Multiple diagrams in the main text and dense annotations in margins.</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_51546611">Imām al-Dīn Riyāz̤ī ibn Luṭf Allāh Muhandis Dihlavī Darbī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_51546611">امام الدّين رياضى ابن لطف الله مهندس دهلوى دربى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23021">Kitāb-i handasah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23021">كتاب هندسه</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1441A-item2">
                     <locus from="23v" to="24r">ff. 23v-24r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1441A(b), ff. 23v-24r.</p>
                        <p>Untitled and incomplete excerpt from an Arabic treatise on the geometry of reflected figures, by an unnamed author.</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1441A-item3">
                     <locus from="24v" to="36v">ff. 24v-36v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1441A(c), ff. 24v-36v .</p>
                        <p>Arabic treatise on optical reality, illusions, perspective and reflections, by 
                <persName key="viaf_51546611" role="aut">Imām al-Dīn Riyāz̤ī ibn Luṭf Allāh Muhandis Dihlavī Darbī</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 36v): completed 1132/1720.</p>
                        <p>Dense annotations.</p>
                        <p>Diagrams; several spaces left blank.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_51546611">Imām al-Dīn Riyāz̤ī ibn Luṭf Allāh Muhandis Dihlavī Darbī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_51546611">امام الدّين رياضى ابن لطف الله مهندس دهلوى دربى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23023">Mirʾāt al-vāqif</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23023">مرآة الواقف</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1441A-item4">
                     <locus from="37v" to="38v">ff. 37v-38v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1441A(d), ff. 37v-38v.</p>
                        <p>Untitled selection of Urdu ghazals by unidentified poets.</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ur">Urdu</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
